context_meta.title: Insider: Lance baits LeBron (again) but controversial late call goes against Pacers
context_meta.summary: Clifton Brown and J. Michael discuss how the Indiana Pacers lost to the Cleveland Cavaliers in Game 4 of their playoff series. INDIANAPOLIS -- Game 4 was an eventful night for Lance Stephenson, but it was not a winning night for the Indiana Pacers. Not only did Stephenson bait LeBron James into a technical foul, the Pacers' mercurial sixth man was a catalyst off the bench, finishing with 11 points and six rebounds. However, once James regained his composure, the Cleveland Cavaliers took control of the game. Outplaying the Pacers during the decisive final six minutes, the Cavaliers prevailed, 104-100, and evened the best-of-seven series at 2-2, heading into  Wednesday night's Game 5 in Cleveland.
